description: The attack on Angoon was one of a series of conflicts between the American military and Alaska Natives in the years after the U.S. bought the territory from Russia in 1867.
title: Navy issues apology for destroying Alaska Native village in 1882

description: It remains unclear what if any authority or impact the synod's final recommendations will have, given the purpose of the exercise was to provide the pope with specific proposals on reform.
title: Catholic church reform process ends without giving more equity to women

description: Jim Donovan called Cleveland's games since the team's expansion rebirth in 1999.
title: Jim Donovan, TV sports anchor, dies of cancer at 68

description: Israel completes retaliatory strikes in Iran; Chef Michael Mina is showcasing foods from his heritage.
title: 10/26: Saturday Morning

description: The strikes risk pushing the archenemies closer to all-out war at a time of spiraling violence across the Middle East, where militant groups backed by Iran — including Hamas in Gaza​ and Hezbollah in Lebanon — are already at war with Israel.
title: Israel and Iran urged to use restraint by world leaders after strikes

description: On Saturday, President Ferdinand Marcos said that many areas remained isolated with people in need of rescue as the death toll climbed to nearly 130 after Tropical Storm Trami.
title: At least 126 dead and missing after landslides, flooding in Philippines

description: The Red Clay Strays is one of music's fastest rising bands. Formed in 2016 in Mobile, Alabama, this rock and roll band fronted by singer Brandon Coleman cuts its teeth playing gigs at local venues across the Southeast. They broke out in 2022 with the release of their debut album. Now, the group was nominated for a CMA award. They released their sophomore album, "Made by These Moments," this summer. Here are The Red Clay Strays with "Disaster."
title: Saturday Sessions: The Red Clay Strays perform "Disaster"

description: Hip hop producer DJ Clark Kent has died after a battle with colon cancer, according to a post on his official social media account. He was 58.
title: DJ Clark Kent, influential hip hop producer, reportedly dies after battle with colon cancer

description: This year, the average person will spend more than $100 on Halloween, with some decorating as early as June. Halloween is no longer one day of candy and costumes for kids.
title: The average person will spend more than $100 on Halloween this year

description: Chef Michael Mina, who opened his first New York City restaurant this year, is showcasing foods from his heritage in the cookbook "My Egypt"
title: Chef Michael Mina is showcasing foods from his heritage

description: For more than a century, AM radio has amassed a rich and storied history. That history includes Beatlemania, fireside chats with President Franklin D. Roosevelt and the Super Bowl. Now, in a world of Instagram, podcasts and TikTok, AM radio is seeking a lifeline.
title: AM radio is seeking a lifeline after a century of storied history

description: Sixty-two years ago this week, 9-year-old Carol Ann Dougherty was murdered inside a Catholic church, steps from her home in Bristol, a suburb of Philadelphia. Despite efforts of investigators, her killer has never been found. Now, the case is getting attention thanks to a new podcast.
title: New podcast highlights Pennsylvania cold case

description: With only 10 days left until Election Day, Beyoncé attended a Houston rally for Vice President Kamala Harris and former President Donald Trump appeared on Joe Rogan's podcast. Both candidates are scheduled to appear in the battleground state of Michigan today.
title: Presidential candidates inject star power into campaigns with 10 days left until Election Day

description: On this edition of CBS Mornings Deals, we show you items that might just become essentials in your everyday life. Visit cbsdeals.com to take advantage of these exclusive deals today. CBS earns commissions on purchases made through cbsdeals.com.
title: Exclusive discounts from CBS Mornings Deals

description: The Baths of Caracalla in Rome were one of the most luxurious spas the world has ever known. Now, for the first time in some 1,500 years, water is back.
title: In Rome, the water is back in the Baths of Caracalla, a luxurious spa

description: With 10 days left until Election Day, more than 35 million Americans have participated in early voting. Of those, more than 19 million have voted by mail. In all, nearly 65 million mail-in ballots have been requested. But election officials in one state found mail-in ballots sent in fraudulently.
title: 35 million Americans have voted early with Election Day around the corner

description: The deadly E.coli outbreak linked to McDonald's quarter pounder hamburgers has infected at least 75 people in 13 states. One person in Colorado has died. The source of the outbreak has not been confirmed.
title: Deadly E.coli outbreak linked to McDonald's has infected at least 75 people in 13 states

description: The FBI is investigating after Chinese government-linked hackers targeted cellphones used by former President Donald Trump and his running mate, JD Vance. CBS News has learned they also targeted the phones or networks used by members of Vice President Kamala Harris' presidential campaign.
title: FBI investigating hackers who targeted cellphones used by Trump, JD Vance

description: A defense official told CBS News that the White House was notified in advance of Israel's attack against Iran.
title: White House notified before Israel's attack on Iran, defense official told CBS News

description: Israel launched a retaliatory strike against Iran. The Israeli military said it conducted precise airstrikes on a number of military targets, including infrastructure across the country, in response to Iran's missile attack earlier this month. The Iranian Army says at least two soldiers were killed in the pre-dawn strikes.
title: Israel completes retaliatory strikes in Iran

description: Israel launched its long-anticipated retaliatory strikes on Iran. Also, a former cardiologist was convicted of drugging and sexually assaulting women he met online. All that and all that matters in today's Eye Opener.
title: Eye Opener: Israel strikes Iran

description: A con artist posing as a wholesale distributor for a major French retailer had made off with $390,000 worth of cheese.
title: Thieves made off with 48,000 pounds of award-winning cheddar

description: Authorities say the election worker told the man that wearing items endorsing a candidate is prohibited at voting sites.
title: Texas man allegedly punched election worker over Trump hat

description: Former President Donald Trump urged two separate courts to toss out the cases brought against him by special counsel Jack Smith.
title: Trump argues Smith unlawfully appointed in documents and election cases

description: Beyoncé, Kelly Rowland, Willie Nelson and Jessica Alba are the latest big-name celebrities to join Vice President Kamala Harris on the campaign trail.
title: Beyoncé endorses Harris for president at Houston rally

description: Face the Nation moderator Bob Schieffer sat down with President George W. Bush in the Oval Office in early 2006 to discuss the ongoing wars in the Middle East and reflect on his time in the White House to date.
title: From the archives: President George W. Bush on "Face the Nation" in 2006

description: Days before the U.S. launched a military operation in Iraq, Vice President Dick Cheney joined Face the Nation. He spoke about the possibility of invasion and international reaction to American foreign policy.
title: From the archives: VP Dick Cheney on potential 2003 invasion of Iraq

description: The attack on an Iranian police convoy in the country's restive southern province of Sistan and Baluchestan killed at least 10 officers, authorities said.
title: Attack on an Iranian police convoy kills at least 10 officers

description: Here's how to bring up the topic productively, according to a relationship expert.
title: Politics is now more important for daters. A relationship expert shares tips.

description: Jill Becher spent more than three years in agonizing pain. After one surgery failed, a riskier treatment provided relief.
title: She was in pain for years. A rare condition was to blame.

description: A dog wows onlookers by walking around town on his two hind legs — but it's not a trick, it's an adaptation. A woman decks out her house in eye-catching decorations each October, not for Halloween but for Breast Cancer Awareness Month. Plus, more heartwarming stories.
title: The Uplift: An adaptable dog

description: Alex Pennig, 32, was shot dead in her St. Paul, Minnesota, apartment. Detectives used surveillance footage to piece together her final moments.
title: Tracking the hours before a young woman became a murder victim

description: In North Carolina, we learn about the growing threat of severe flooding facing inland communities. And in Connecticut, we check in at the only hotel in the country that runs entirely on renewable electricity. Watch these stories and more on "Eye on America" with host Michelle Miller.
title: Eye on America: New hotel runs on clean energy, and growing threats of inland flooding

description: China-backed hackers targeted Trump, Vance, sources say; Clemson fraternity embraces student in intellectual disability program
title: 10/25: CBS Evening News
